---
// src/pages/privacy.astro
// Privacy stub. Real attorney-reviewed copy lands before public launch.
// The third party list reflects Clean's actual stack today.
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
---

<Legal title="Privacy Policy" updatedAt="May 2026" description="How Dog Gone Clean handles your information.">
  <p>
    <em>This document is a draft. Final attorney-reviewed copy lands
    before the Hurricane Bath service opens to bookings in The Villages.</em>
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>
    When you book a Hurricane Bath visit, we collect your name, the
    service address inside The Villages, contact details (phone and
    email), your dog's name, breed, and coat notes, and payment
    information processed by our payment provider. When you visit this
    site, your browser sends standard technical information (IP address,
    browser type, pages viewed).
  </p>

  <h2>What we do with it</h2>
  <p>
    We use this information to schedule and provide the service, process
    payments, send service related communications, and meet our legal
    obligations. We do not sell your data, and we do not share it with
    third parties for marketing.
  </p>

  <h2>Third parties we use</h2>
  <p>
    Dog Gone Clean uses the following services to operate: Stripe
    (payments), Twilio (SMS), Resend (email), Google (sign in and
    business email), Supabase (data storage), DigitalOcean (hosting).
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Mobile phone numbers, SMS consent, and text message content
    are never shared with third parties for marketing purposes.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Your card on file</h2>
  <p>
    Card details are stored with Stripe, never on our servers. We retain
    only the tokenized reference Stripe gives us so we can charge for
    your scheduled visits. You can update or remove your card on file
    from the client portal at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable measures to protect the information we hold. No
    system is perfectly secure.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy: contact details land before launch.
  </p>
</Legal>
